 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucougarpak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cougar Pak</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/11/02 1:32:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3713.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.pakcafan.com/daoc/images/cougsig2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> Diagree holeheartedly on assasins' role at forts.<br>
<br>
On the attack, we can still be deadly, regardless of some puny AE'ing caster, just go up from a different climb point and drop him -- most casters ignore the back climb points. Use them.<br>
<br>
On the defense, we can always be anti-assasin defense up on the walls with our crippling poisons. Myself though, I have found that stealthing up, porting out PA'ing and porting back in at the gatekeeper has much more effect. So much so that the attackers usually curse my name - and I'm getting well known for that tactic on my server.<br>
<br>
I love keep fighting with my shade, and I usually get alot of RPs each time I'm there. So again, I heartily disagree with your assertion that our role is disappearing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugalium.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Galium</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/11/02 2:13:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3713.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> First off I point out you are a nightshade and you are not facing anywhere close to the same amount of PBAOE/GTAOE/AOE/Instant CCs as shadowblades and infiltrators are facing. Second I was pointing out various aspects of the entire picture, and the things that have occured to the assassins classes in the last while, not just our roles within keeps.<br>
<br>
However looking at our roles in the keeps the other day every single climb spot on a keep had a low level pbaoer inside along the wall simply nuking the entire battle. Not up where you can reach them, but down in the courtyard just hitting the base of the climb spot. Thats not normal though, so yea you can go up the back routes, that works great except with 50 players on the doors, but still I can get inside.<br>
<br>
What then? I am not talking about lightly defended keeps, sure we have effectiveness there, I am talking about real defense by a decent group(s). The enemy is often huddled over by the climbing routes I couldnt get up to start, thus getting anywhere close means I get pbaoe/gtaoe. I can drop down into the courtyard and go wack the GTAOE'er, PBAOE'er and tanks down there in a suicide dash, I may even get two folks if I am lucky and they are not, hell if I am really lucky I can Vanish and get someone else. Ok I got my target(s) and now I am dead and out of the fight till we get through the doors.... oh wait my target just got a res, oh there he goes GTAOEing already. One for one, when the other can get ressed quickly is not a fair trade. The only time I find this is particilarily effective is if the doors are about to come down, they may not get ressed and even if they are they have res sickness for the lord room defense. If the ressers are stupid enough you might kill them and then go for the GTAOEers, unfortunetly they are not all that stupid.<br>
<br>
No offense but a role and a meaningful role are different things. The bottom line, and the point of my original comments is that overall we have lost effectiveness not gained, or remained stable. That isnt to say I disagree with all the things we have lost, but when nothing good comes in return, when other classes continue to become more powerful... we dwindle in effectiveness. <br>
<br>
Culdor<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucougarpak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cougar Pak</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/11/02 3:17:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3713.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.pakcafan.com/daoc/images/cougsig2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> Perhaps I don't face as many as other assasins, with SMs just getting their PBAE, and Ice Wizzies hardly in abundance, however there are plenty of GTAE'ers I need to worry about, and instant CC classes. But for me, when I know there is someone doing that stuff, I just stand on top of the climb point and use my Castable DD (or throwing knives or xbows what have you) and make them scurry for thier little lives. This free's up my teammates to climb up behind me as I drop down and restealth to take up the vaccuum left by that scurrying pain in my ass.<br>
<br>
I LOVE keep attacks and defenses, I go out of my way to create them (www.pakcafan.com/daoc), being a guildleader I can do that <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . If a siege doesn't last at least 1 hour it isn't fun for me (well maybe not NOT fun, but I much rather enjoy the long drawn out sieges). In those long sieges you learn how to stay alive and maximize your attacking. A hib fort is the easiest thing in the world to attack for an assasin, and I pity the people who stand on top of the ramparts thinking they can defeat me - they can't.  Albion and Midgard keeps are a bit harder, but in knowing how to use the climbpoints and tops of the ramparts, you can give yourself good positions as well.<br>
<br>
There is no other class that can climb walls and penetrate the defenses of a defending force other than assasins, therefore how can we dwindle in effectiveness when we still do it with abundance? I have been known to singlehandedly clear entire ramparts (hib forts) and in a team of nightshades we've also cleared entire ramparts of albion and midgard keeps.<br>
<br>
Courtyard casters a problem? Call in your own GTAE'ers or call in treb fire (you know, siege weapons are usefull) on the spot that dumb ass caster is making your life miserable. Hell, I'll stand on top of the walls (to the sides of the climb point) and I'll rain down my DDs on them till they flee for cover or someone starts attacking me. Do you think casters like having a big fat bullseye on their chest? No, but you have to put it there for them. You need to put the hurt on anyone preventing you from doing your job. And sometimes we can't do that alone, we need teamwork for that. That has ZERO impact on our overall usefullness. In fact it merely creates a roll for us to play, expanding our roles in keep attacks.<br>
<br>
In any effect, this post has gone way off the original target, and I could talk at length about sieging and defending as it is a favorite of mine (and one I'm well skilled at). If anyone wants to chat with me in game about these tactics(assasins only please <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) My character is named Grollo on the Galahad server. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubaym.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Baym</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/12/02 8:51:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3713.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> My latest minstrel encounter was Eboo (level 50) on Galahad. Not only did I get perf off, but he NEVER casted on me at all. He simply meleed me. My best melee attack was doublefrost which did 68 (yes 68, btw I am 46 with LA of 44 with bonuses and using arcanium weapons). Not a single one of his attacks hit for less than 150. At the end of the fight, I had barely taken off 1/3 of his health. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#FF0000>- </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse>The Safehouse</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19>Main Hall</a> <font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href="http://www.thesafehouse.org">The Safehouse website</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font> <center><a href="http://www.guildboss.com"><img
